jillo'' (1955) Caribbean Library</ref> |- | [[Sun Yat-sen]] || || Republic of China || 1917-1918, 1922 ||Technically as ''Grand Marshal''<ref>{{cite book|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=otwbBh_GgrwC&pg=PA255&dq=tang+jiyao&hl=en&ei=TSraTNfHMMT6lwfry7XNCQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CD4Q6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=tang%20jiyao&f=false|title=Wu Tingfang (1842-1922): reform and modernization in modern Chinese history|author=Linda Pomerantz-Zhang|year=1992|publisher=Hong Kong University Press|location=|page=255|isbn=962209287X|pages=|accessdate=2010-10-31}}</ref> <small>(<small>[[Talk:Generalissimo#Sun Yat-Sen|source does not support this]]</small>)</small> |- | {{sortname|Antonio|López de Santa Anna}} || [[Mexican Army]] || Mexico ||1846-1855||<ref>Stephen L Hardin, Angus McBride : ''The Alamo 1836'' (2001) Osprey . pp24, 100 </ref> |}
